<paragraph blockId="73.[151,1436,1827,2031]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,433,1827,1852]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" reason="1">Comparative diagnosis.</emphasis>
The closest species to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Raines &amp; Huber" authorityYear="2012" box="[692,816,1828,1851]" class="Bivalvia" family="Tellinidae" genus="Herouvalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="rapanui">
<emphasis box="[692,816,1828,1851]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">H. rapanui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are its two described congeners, the widely distributed 
<taxonomicName authority="A. Adams, 1854" authorityName="A. Adams" authorityYear="1854" box="[151,696,1863,1887]" class="Bivalvia" family="Veneridae" genus="Gafrarium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Venerida" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="caelatum" subGenus="Corbis">
<emphasis box="[151,271,1863,1887]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Gafrarium</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[291,367,1863,1887]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Corbis</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[388,490,1863,1887]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">caelatum</emphasis>
A. 
<bibRefCitation author="Adams, A." box="[541,696,1863,1887]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="69 - 74" refId="ref50730" refString="Adams, A. (1854) Descriptions of new shells from the collection of H. Cuming, Esq. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, (21), 69 - 74." type="journal article" year="1854">Adams, 1854</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, (syn. 
<taxonomicName authority="Gould, 1861" authorityName="Gould" authorityYear="1861" box="[779,1122,1863,1887]" class="Bivalvia" family="Tellinidae" genus="Tellina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="euglypta">
<emphasis box="[779,963,1863,1887]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Tellina euglypta</emphasis>
